<!---

Johny has fallen in love with an attractive girl called Parmida since one year ago...

Today, Johny set up a meeting with his partner in a romantic garden. Unfortunately, Johny has forgotten where the garden is. But he remembers that the garden looks like a `square` with sides parallel to the coordinate axes. He also remembers that there is exactly `one tree on each vertex of the square`. Now, Johny knows the position of only 2 of the trees. Help him to find the position of 2 remaining ones.

# Input:

The input contains two pairs of coordinates:
```csharp
0 0 0 1
```
Where first two numbers are coordinates of the first tree. And second two numbers are coordinates of the second tree. Be careful,  ` !Numbers can be negative`

# Your task, Daniel-san:
Return two pairs of coordinates that correspond to the coordinates of the two other trees. If there is no solution, return `-1` ;

```csharp
Garden.Trees(0, 0, 1, 1) ==  "0 1 1 0";
Garden.Trees(0, 0, 0, 1) ==  "1 0 1 1";
Garden.Trees(0, 0, 1, 2) ==  "-1";
```

--->
